# Frontend client ŌĆö FSD folder structure

Root: **`src/`**.

## Top-level layout

| Path                                      | Purpose                                                                       |
| ----------------------------------------- | ----------------------------------------------------------------------------- | --------------------------- |
| `src/pages/`                              | Route-level / screen composition                                              |
| `src/features/<name>/`                    | Feature slice: `ui/`, `model/`, `lib/`                                        |
| `src/providers/`                          | App-wide providers                                                            |
| `src/assets/images/`, `icons/`, `videos/` | Static media                                                                  |
| `src/shared/components/`                  | Reusable UI                                                                   | `dynamic-settings-form.tsx` |
| `src/shared/utils/`                       | Cross-feature helpers (`utils.ts`, `api.ts`, ŌĆ”)                               |
| `src/shared/constants/`                   | Shared constants                                                              |
| `src/shared/types/`                       | Cross-feature types (e.g. `api.ts` for `BaseApiResponse`)                     |
| `src/shared/hooks/`                       | Cross-feature hooks (e.g. `useMediaQuery.ts`)                                 |
| `src/shared/services/`                    | Shared infrastructure; e.g. `base-api.service.ts`, `api/` for base HTTP layer |

## Feature slice (`src/features/<feature>/`)

- **`ui/`** ŌĆö components for this feature only.
- **`model/`** ŌĆö state and data access:
  - **`model/hooks/`** ŌĆö feature hooks (e.g. `useUsers.ts`).
  - **`model/api/`** ŌĆö feature API modules (e.g. `users.api.ts`) as classes/methods that use the shared base API service.
- **`lib/`** ŌĆö feature-only pure code:
  - **`lib/utils.ts`** ŌĆö feature logic (e.g. `combineUserSettings`).
  - **`lib/types.ts`** ŌĆö feature-only types (e.g. `BaseUser`).

Use **plural** feature folder names when they represent a domain aggregate (`users`, `accounts`), unless the codebase already standardizes on singular.

## Placement rules (feature vs shared)

| Kind                 | Feature-specific                                                     | Shared / general                                   |
| -------------------- | -------------------------------------------------------------------- | -------------------------------------------------- |
| Pure logic / helpers | `features/<f>/lib/utils.ts`                                          | `shared/utils/utils.ts` or `shared/utils/api.ts`   |
| Types                | `features/<f>/lib/types.ts`                                          | `shared/types/<topic>.ts` (e.g. `api.ts`)          |
| Stateful hooks       | `features/<f>/model/hooks/useX.ts`                                   | `shared/hooks/useX.ts`                             |
| HTTP / API classes   | `features/<f>/model/api/<f>.api.ts` (compose `shared/services` base) | `shared/services/` (base client, shared endpoints) |

**Default:** If it is used only by one feature, keep it under that feature. If two or more features need it, promote to `shared/` (or extract a shared submodule).

## Imports

Prefer **stable public paths** (e.g. `@/shared/...`, `@/features/users/...`) if the bundler/tsconfig defines them; avoid deep relative chains across slices when an alias exists.
